  aggravating factors present but no mitigating factors); <span class="cite">In re: Bankston, 01-1352 (La. 6/29/01),
  <a href="2001-06-29_2001-1352.htm">791 So. 2d 1263</a></span> (one year and one day suspension imposed for failure to
  communicate with a client, failure to account for or refund unearned fee, and failure to cooperate with the ODC;
  numerous aggravating factors present but no mitigating factors); <span class="cite">In re: Turnage, 01-1240 (La.
  6/22/01), <a href="2001-06-22_2001-1240.htm">790 So. 2d 620</a></span> (one year and one day suspension imposed for
